{"questionId":"22591699","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>In parts (b) and (c), consider two non-constant functions, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>≠</mo><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>By rearranging the equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>, show that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenc